OL,5, A lack of PPE during the Covid pandemic
OL,6, meant some GPs wore repurposed bin bags
OL,7, for aprons, a public inquiry has heard.
OL,9,FDr Chris Williams, deputy chairman of  
OL,10,Fthe Royal College of GPs, told the     
OL,11,FScottish Covid Inquiry that doctors    
OL,12,Ffelt they did not have the "tools for  
OL,13,Fthe job" early on in the pandemic.     
OL,15,FDr Williams said there was a feeling   
OL,16,Fthe PPE guidance was based on what was 
OL,17,Favailable rather than appropriate.     
OL,19,FSome GPs also bought higher-grade face 
OL,20,Fmasks online instead of using NHS ones.
